HEADWORD: Salvable
<hw>Sal"va*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>salvare</ets> to save, from <ets>salvus</ets> safe. Cf.
<er>Savable</er>.]</ety> <def>Capable of being saved; admitting of
salvation.</def> <rj><au>Dr. H. More.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sal"va*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
